html tags

Document Structure:

<html>: Defines the root of an HTML document.
<head>: Contains meta-information about the HTML document (e.g., title, meta tags).
<title>: Sets the title of the HTML document, displayed in the browser's title bar or tab.
<body>: Contains the content of the HTML document.
Text Formatting:

<h1> to <h6>: Heading tags for defining headings (h1 being the largest and h6 the smallest).
<p>: Defines a paragraph.
<strong> or <b>: Represents strong importance or bold text.
<em> or <i>: Represents emphasized text or italic text.
<u>: Represents underlined text (though not recommended for styling).
Lists:

<ul>: Defines an unordered (bulleted) list.
<ol>: Defines an ordered (numbered) list.
<li>: Represents a list item.
Links:

<a>: Defines a hyperlink.
href: Specifies the URL the link goes to.
target="_blank": Opens the linked document in a new tab or window.
Images:

<img>: Embeds an image.
src: Specifies the path to the image file.
alt: Provides alternative text for accessibility.
Tables:

<table>: Defines a table.
<tr>: Defines a table row.
<td>: Defines a table cell (data).
<th>: Defines a table header cell.
Forms:

<form>: Defines an HTML form for user input.
<input>: Defines an input field.
<textarea>: Defines a multiline text input.
<select>: Defines a dropdown list.
<button>: Defines a clickable button.
Media:

<audio>: Embeds audio content.
<video>: Embeds video content.
<iframe>: Embeds an inline frame (used for embedding external content, like maps or videos).
Style and Layout:

<div>: Defines a division or a section in an HTML document.
<span>: Defines an inline container for styling a specific portion of text.
<br>: Represents a line break.
<hr>: Represents a horizontal rule (line).
Meta Information:

<meta>: Provides metadata about the HTML document (e.g., character set, viewport settings).


CSS 
Text Styling:

color: Sets the color of the text.
font-family: Specifies the font for text.
font-size: Sets the size of the font.
font-weight: Defines the thickness of the font characters (e.g., bold).
Text Layout:

text-align: Aligns text (left, right, center, justify).
line-height: Sets the height of a line of text.
letter-spacing: Adjusts the spacing between characters.
text-decoration: Adds decoration to text (e.g., underline, overline, line-through).
Backgrounds:

background-color: Sets the background color.
background-image: Sets the background image.
background-size: Sets the size of the background image.
background-position: Sets the starting position of the background image.
Borders:

border: Sets the border properties (width, style, color).
border-radius: Adds rounded corners to an element.
Margins, Padding, and Dimensions:

margin: Sets the margin outside an element.
padding: Sets the padding inside an element.
width: Sets the width of an element.
height: Sets the height of an element.
Positioning:

position: Sets the positioning method (e.g., relative, absolute, fixed).
top, right, bottom, left: Sets the positioning values.
Display:

display: Defines how an element is displayed (e.g., block, inline, none).
flex: Enables a flex container.
justify-content: Aligns items on the main axis in a flex container.
Flexbox:

flex-direction: Sets the direction of the main axis in a flex container.
align-items: Aligns items on the cross axis in a flex container.
flex-grow, flex-shrink, flex-basis: Controls the flexibility of a flex item.
Grid Layout:

display: grid: Enables a grid container.
grid-template-columns, grid-template-rows: Defines the columns and rows of a grid.
Transformations and Transitions:

transform: Applies a 2D or 3D transformation to an element.
transition: Specifies how a property should transition over time.
Box Model:

box-sizing: Defines how the width and height of an element are calculated.
outline: Sets the outline properties (width, style, color).
Visibility and Opacity:

visibility: Sets whether an element is visible or hidden.
opacity: Sets the opacity level of an element.